        <title>Course Participant Introductions</title>
        <contents>&lt;div style="width: 716px;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Research, and likely your own experiences, indicate that the strength of classroom connections (teacher-student and student-student) have a direct effect on motivation, retention, and learning. It is important then, for learners to get to know and feel comfortable with both their instructor(s) and their peers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img width="54" height="50" style="float: left; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" alt="Reflection icon - dark head profile with puzzle brain" src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/LTA-EI-Reflecticonsm.jpg" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Can you think of one or more examples from your own experiences that support these statements?  In what ways are peer relationships important in your classroom?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Research also notes that online learning often presents barriers to the creation of these important &lt;em&gt;classroom connections&lt;/em&gt;. Throughout this course, we have provided &lt;strong&gt;Discussion Forum activities&lt;/strong&gt; in order to foster practitioner networks and learning relationships. We strongly encourage you to not only share your ideas and experiences, but also to read and respond to others in the course in order to strengthen your learning experience and build your professional learning network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To get started making these connections, the next course activity asks everyone to help build a sense of &lt;em&gt;online community&lt;/em&gt; by introducing yourselves and getting to know others in the course. In your introduction, we ask that you share with others:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;your name, location and a bit about your learners;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;any experience(s) you've had using Explicit Instruction; and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;your thoughts regarding the needs, concerns, and goals that drew you to participate in this course.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We look forward to virtually meeting you via the discussion!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #993300;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Click Next to end this lesson, return to the Main Course Menu, and access the Discussion Forum to post your introduction. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #993300;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</contents>
